article.headline: James Madison 45, VMI 17
article.story: HARRISONBURG, Va. (AP) -- L.C. Baker scored on a 36-yard pass and a 42-yard run as James Madison built a four-touchdown lead early in the third quarter and coasted over VMI 45-17 on Saturday. Quarterback Rodney Landers, who totaled 369 yards of total offense in last week's win against New Hampshire, let the ground game take over against the Keydets (1-2). Jamal Sullivan led the 298-yard running attack with 83 yards and a touchdown, a 44-yard run to put the Dukes (2-1) up 7-0 in the first quarter. Baker totaled 60 yards, including the 42-yard dash to open the second half and put James Madison up 28-0. He finished with 79 yards receiving. Antoinne Bolton had touchdown runs of 3 and 2 yards. He finished with 48 yards. Landers had 123 yards in the air on 8-of-10 passing and gained 41 yards on the ground. VMI did all their scoring in the second half. Howard Abegesah run in from 27 yards out to score in the fourth quarter and Tim Maypray returned a kickoff 86 yards to close out the scoring. Abegesah finished with 71 yards on 19 carries and Maypray at 61 receiving yards.
